  <title>Quantum Mathematics</title>

  <introduction>
    <p>
      We have been using the visual representation to build intuition about
      quantum state and quantum gates. This representation is limited in 
      two important ways:
    </p>
    <p>
    <ul>
      <li>It does not fully explain crucial phase behavior.</li>
      <li>It can only represent simple states with small ratios.</li>
    </ul>
    </p>
    <p> In this chapter, we have three learning goals:</p>
     <p>
    <ul>
      <li>The meaning and calculations for independent probabilities</li>
      <li>Mathematical notation for single and multi-qubit quantum state </li>
      <li>Mathematical operations to calculate the output of quantum gates (operations)</li>
    </ul>
    </p>
  </introduction>

